<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-032-232 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 600 162</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  Oct 17 1991 v36 n21A p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Graphics board makers anoint Microsoft; but IBM'sregister-conscious graphics modes will live on as developers tiein to the CPU bus. (Microsoft Corp's Windows graphical userinterface is standard of choice for board makers at the ComdexFall 1991 trade show)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Harbert, Tammi.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Graphics board vendors will show their support of the MicrosoftWindows graphical user interface (GUI) at the upcoming Comdex Falltrade show by introducing boards that opt for fixed-functionhardware accelerator chips or programmable processors.andP;  Suchdevices speed refresh rates, offer deeper colors, handle higherresolutions and speed graphics processing.andP;  Traditional methodsfor attaining higher graphics performance involve writing directlyto the hardware registers of graphics controller chips.andP;  Today,Windows 3.0 and similar GUIs allow developers to write to standardsoftware interfaces, which frees board makers from register-basedstandards.andP;  Actix Systems Inc, CSS Laboratories and Genoa SystemsCorp are among the companies which will offer accelerator chips orprogrammable processor designs at Comdex.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   Microsoft Windows (Graphical user interface) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Graphics boards/cardsGraphical user interfaceAccelerator boards/cardsNew ProductConferences and MeetingsProgrammable ControllersProcessor ArchitecturePerformance ImprovementVendorsComdex-Fall.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>